1. Core Architecture Components

package com.company.chatbot.core;

import opennlp.tools.tokenize.Tokenizer;
import opennlp.tools.postag.POSTagger;
import opennlp.tools.namefind.NameFinderME;
import opennlp.tools.sentdetect.SentenceDetector;

public class ChatbotEngine {
    private PreprocessingPipeline preprocessor;
    private IntentClassifier intentClassifier;
    private EntityExtractor entityExtractor;
    private ContextManager contextManager;
    private ResponseGenerator responseGenerator;
    private ConversationManager conversationManager;
    
    public ChatbotResponse processQuery(String userInput, String sessionId) {
        // Main processing pipeline
        ProcessedInput processed = preprocessor.process(userInput);
        Intent intent = intentClassifier.classify(processed);
        List<Entity> entities = entityExtractor.extract(processed);
        Context context = contextManager.getContext(sessionId);
        
        QueryRequest request = new QueryRequest(intent, entities, context);
        return responseGenerator.generateResponse(request);
    }
}

2. Enhanced Preprocessing Pipeline

package com.company.chatbot.preprocessing;

import opennlp.tools.tokenize.TokenizerME;
import opennlp.tools.tokenize.TokenizerModel;
import opennlp.tools.postag.POSTaggerME;
import opennlp.tools.postag.POSModel;

public class PreprocessingPipeline {
    private TokenizerME tokenizer;
    private POSTaggerME posTagger;
    private TextNormalizer normalizer;
    private SpellChecker spellChecker;
    
    public ProcessedInput process(String input) {
        // 1. Text normalization
        String normalized = normalizer.normalize(input);
        
        // 2. Spell checking and correction
        String corrected = spellChecker.correct(normalized);
        
        // 3. Tokenization
        String[] tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(corrected);
        
        // 4. POS tagging
        String[] posTags = posTagger.tag(tokens);
        
        // 5. Lemmatization
        String[] lemmas = lemmatize(tokens, posTags);
        
        return new ProcessedInput(corrected, tokens, posTags, lemmas);
    }
    
    private String[] lemmatize(String[] tokens, String[] posTags) {
        // Implement lemmatization logic
        return tokens; // Simplified
    }
}

3. Multi-layered Intent Classification

package com.company.chatbot.intent;

import opennlp.tools.doccat.DoccatME;
import opennlp.tools.doccat.DoccatModel;

public class IntentClassifier {
    private DoccatME categorizer;
    private PatternMatcher patternMatcher;
    private KeywordMatcher keywordMatcher;
    
    public Intent classify(ProcessedInput input) {
        // Layer 1: Pattern-based classification
        Intent patternIntent = patternMatcher.match(input);
        if (patternIntent.getConfidence() > 0.8) {
            return patternIntent;
        }
        
        // Layer 2: Keyword-based classification
        Intent keywordIntent = keywordMatcher.match(input);
        if (keywordIntent.getConfidence() > 0.7) {
            return keywordIntent;
        }
        
        // Layer 3: ML-based classification using OpenNLP
        double[] outcomes = categorizer.categorize(input.getTokens());
        String category = categorizer.getBestCategory(outcomes);
        double confidence = categorizer.getMaxConfidence(outcomes);
        
        return new Intent(IntentType.valueOf(category.toUpperCase()), confidence);
    }
}
IntentClassifier.java

4. Advanced Entity Extraction

package com.company.chatbot.entity;

import opennlp.tools.namefind.NameFinderME;
import opennlp.tools.namefind.TokenNameFinderModel;
import opennlp.tools.util.Span;

public class EntityExtractor {
    private NameFinderME contractNumberFinder;
    private NameFinderME customerNameFinder;
    private NameFinderME partNumberFinder;
    private NameFinderME personNameFinder;
    private RegexEntityExtractor regexExtractor;
    
    public List<Entity> extract(ProcessedInput input) {
        List<Entity> entities = new ArrayList<>();
        String[] tokens = input.getTokens();
        
        // Extract contract numbers
        Span[] contractSpans = contractNumberFinder.find(tokens);
        entities.addAll(createEntities(contractSpans, tokens, EntityType.CONTRACT_NUMBER));
        
        // Extract customer names
        Span[] customerSpans = customerNameFinder.find(tokens);
        entities.addAll(createEntities(customerSpans, tokens, EntityType.CUSTOMER_NAME));
        
        // Extract part numbers
        Span[] partSpans = partNumberFinder.find(tokens);
        entities.addAll(createEntities(partSpans, tokens, EntityType.PART_NUMBER));
        
        // Extract person names
        Span[] personSpans = personNameFinder.find(tokens);
        entities.addAll(createEntities(personSpans, tokens, EntityType.PERSON_NAME));
        
        // Regex-based extraction for specific patterns
        entities.addAll(regexExtractor.extract(input.getOriginalText()));
        
        return entities;
    }
    
    private List<Entity> createEntities(Span[] spans, String[] tokens, EntityType type) {
        List<Entity> entities = new ArrayList<>();
        for (Span span : spans) {
            String value = String.join(" ", Arrays.copyOfRange(tokens, span.getStart(), span.getEnd()));
            entities.add(new Entity(type, value, span.getProb()));
        }
        return entities;
    }
}
EntityExtractor.java

5. Context Resolution System

package com.company.chatbot.context;

import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class ContextManager {
    private Map<String, ConversationContext> sessionContexts = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
    
    public Context getContext(String sessionId) {
        return sessionContexts.computeIfAbsent(sessionId, k -> new ConversationContext());
    }
    
    public void updateContext(String sessionId, Intent intent, List<Entity> entities, String response) {
        ConversationContext context = (ConversationContext) getContext(sessionId);
        context.addInteraction(new Interaction(intent, entities, response));
        context.updateLastActivity();
    }
    
    public void clearContext(String sessionId) {
        sessionContexts.remove(sessionId);
    }
}

package com.company.chatbot.conversation;

public class ConversationManager {
    private ContextManager contextManager;
    private ClarificationHandler clarificationHandler;
    
    public ChatbotResponse handleConversation(String userInput, String sessionId) {
        ConversationContext context = (ConversationContext) contextManager.getContext(sessionId);
        
        // Check if we're in a clarification flow
        if (context.isWaitingForClarification()) {
            return clarificationHandler.handleClarificationResponse(userInput, context);
        }
        
        // Check for follow-up questions
        if (context.hasRecentInteraction()) {
            return handleFollowUp(userInput, context);
        }
        
        // Regular processing
        return processNewQuery(userInput, sessionId);
    }

}

8. Clarification Handler

package com.company.chatbot.clarification;

public class ClarificationHandler {
    
    public ChatbotResponse handleAmbiguousQuery(QueryRequest request) {
        List<String> clarificationOptions = generateClarificationOptions(request);
        
        if (clarificationOptions.size() > 1) {
            return createClarificationResponse(clarificationOptions);
        }
        
        return null; // No clarification needed
    }
    
    public ChatbotResponse handleClarificationResponse(String userInput, ConversationContext context) {
        // Parse user's clarification choice
        int choice = parseChoice(userInput);
        
        if (choice > 0 && choice <= context.getClarificationOptions().size()) {
            String selectedOption = context.getClarificationOptions().get(choice - 1);
            return processClarifiedQuery(selectedOption, context);
        }
        
        return createInvalidChoiceResponse();
    }
    
    private List<String> generateClarificationOptions(QueryRequest request) {
        List<String> options = new ArrayList<>();
        
        // Generate options based on ambiguous entities or intents
        if (request.getIntent().getConfidence() < 0.6) {
            options.addAll(generateIntentOptions(request));
        }
        
        if (hasAmbiguousEntities(request.getEntities())) {
            options.addAll(generateEntityOptions(request.getEntities()));
        }
        
        return options;
    }
}

9. Enhanced Response Generator

package com.company.chatbot.response;

public class ResponseGenerator {
    private DatabaseService databaseService;
    private TemplateEngine templateEngine;
    private ResponseFormatter formatter;
    
    public ChatbotResponse generateResponse(QueryRequest request) {
        try {
            switch (request.getIntent().getType()) {
                case CONTRACT_DETAILS:
                    return handleContractDetails(request);
                case CONTRACT_SEARCH:
                    return handleContractSearch(request);
                case PART_SPECIFICATIONS:
                    return handlePartSpecifications(request);
                case CUSTOMER_CONTRACTS:
                    return handleCustomerContracts(request);
                // Add more cases for all intent types
                default:
                    return createUnknownIntentResponse();
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return createErrorResponse(e.getMessage());
        }
    }
    
    private ChatbotResponse handleContractDetails(QueryRequest request) {
        String contractNumber = extractContractNumber(request.getEntities());
        
        if (contractNumber == null) {
            return createMissingParameterResponse("contract number");
        }
        
        ContractDetails contract = databaseService.getContractDetails(contractNumber);
        
        if (contract == null) {
            return createNotFoundResponse("Contract", contractNumber);
        }
        
        String response = templateEngine.format("contract_details_template", contract);
        return new ChatbotResponse(response, ResponseType.SUCCESS, contract);
    }
    
    private ChatbotResponse handlePartSpecifications(QueryRequest request) {
        String partNumber = extractPartNumber(request.getEntities());
        
        if (partNumber == null) {
            return createMissingParameterResponse("part number");
        }
        
        PartSpecification spec = databaseService.getPartSpecifications(partNumber);
        
        if (spec == null) {
            return createNotFoundResponse("Part", partNumber);
        }
        
        String response = templateEngine.format("part_specifications_template", spec);
        return new ChatbotResponse(response, ResponseType.SUCCESS, spec);
    }
}
ResponseGenerator.java
